      </li>
      <li>Into eighths. The 8 on the bottom of the fraction tells us how many parts the whole, or the part from 0 to 1 is split into.</li>
      <li>The first numbers were all less than 1, the second numbers were all greater than 1. In the first numbers, the top part of the fraction was a smaller number than the bottom part. In the second numbers, the top part was bigger than the bottom part.</li>
    </ol>
